echo "Tools-    brakeman(Windows and Linux)- Brakeman is a static analysis security vulnerability scanner for Ruby on Rails applications.
                bruteforce(Windows and Linux)- Brute force attacks are usually used to obtain personal information such as passwords, passphrases, etc.
                entropy(Windows and Linux)- It is a simple tool to test entropy of a file.
                extundelete(Windows and Linux)- extundelete is designed to undelete files from an unmounted partition to a separate (mounted) partition.
                pngtools(Windows)- It dumps information on a PNG files.
                pyunpack(Linux)- It is a unpacker for packed Python executables.
                shoe(Windows and Linux)- A simple tool to assist with TCP remote communication.
                swftools(Windows and Linux)- SWFTools is a collection of utilities for working with Adobe Flash files (SWF files).
                wordlist(Windows and Linux)- A wordlist is essentially a list of passwords that are collected in plain text."